com.pump.jar

Class MissingJarUserResponseManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pump.jar.MissingJarPreferenceResponseManager
      • com.pump.jar.MissingJarUserResponseManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MissingJarResponseManager

    public class MissingJarUserResponseManager
extends MissingJarPreferenceResponseManager
    When creating a jar we have to decide what to do with external jar dependencies: should we disregard them (like we should sure javax.jnlp.* classes), copy the entire jar (like we should for JFreeChart), or copy only the specific classes we need?

    This class helps manage this decision.

      • resolveBehaviors

        public void resolveBehaviors(MissingJarResponseManager manager,
                             java.util.Map<java.io.File,MissingJarResponse> requiredJars,
                             java.util.Set<java.io.File> keySet,
                             java.lang.String name)
        Show a modal dialog prompting the user to associate a Behavior to one or more jar Files.

        This "OK" button on this dialog is disabled until a behavior is chosen for each file.

        Specified by:
        resolveBehaviors in interface MissingJarResponseManager
        Overrides:
        resolveBehaviors in class MissingJarPreferenceResponseManager
        Parameters:
        choiceModel - the choice model used.
        jarBehaviors - known jar behaviors. This is where the users choices will be stored, so it may be empty but it can not be null. This is also used to set up the dialog if you want to preset certain choices.
        jarFiles - the set of jar files that the user will make choices for. When this dialog is dismissed it is guaranteed that the jarBehaviors map will have a non-null value associated with each of these Files.
        primaryClassName - the UI needs the name of the compiled class to explain things to the user.
